      Start of Main Content Publications


   ERIC Calendar of Education-Related Conferences -- Includes more than
   700 international, national, regional, and state conferences scheduled
   for this year and next year. The Calendar can be searched by keyword;
   sponsor; and conference name, date, and location.
   The ERIC Review -- Provides teachers, counselors, and administrators
   with information about emerging education issues; announces important
   ERIC developments and new products and services; and presents recent
   research findings.
   Getting Online: A Friendly Guide for Teachers, Students, and Parents --
   Explains the basics of accessing the Internet.
   Parent Brochures -- Offer answers to commonly asked questions from
   parents and teachers.
   Striving for Excellence -- Presents several ERIC Digests that outline
   issues, programs, and research related to the seven education
   priorities established by the President and the Secretary of the U.S.
   Department of Education.

            For more publications, visit the About ERIC section.

